To include smoke group and exclude sanity group in TestNG, configure both in your testng.xml:

ðŸ”¹ testng.xml Example:

<suite name="Suite">
  <test name="SmokeOnly">
    <groups>
      <run>
        <include name="smoke"/>
        <exclude name="sanity"/>
      </run>
    </groups>
    <classes>
      <class name="tests.SampleTest"/>
    </classes>
  </test>
</suite>

@Test(groups = {"sanity", "smoke"})
public void testLogin() {
    System.out.println("This test belongs to both sanity and smoke groups");
}


âœ… Only tests in smoke group (and not in sanity) will run.
